# InsureTech Go SDK

Official Go SDK for the InsureTech Platform API

[![Go Version](https://img.shields.io/badge/go-%3E%3D1.19-blue)](https://golang.org/dl/)
[![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-green)](LICENSE)
[![Documentation](https://img.shields.io/badge/docs-latest-brightgreen)](https://docs.insuretech.com)

## Features

- 🔐 Secure authentication (API Key & OAuth2)
- 📦 Complete API coverage for all InsureTech services
- 🔄 Automatic retry with exponential backoff
- ⚡ Context-aware with timeout support
- 📄 Pagination support for list operations
- 🛡️ Type-safe request/response models
- 🐛 Detailed error handling
- 📚 Comprehensive documentation

## Installation

```bash
go get github.com/insuretech/go-sdk
```

## Quick Start

```go
package main

import (
    "context"
    "fmt"
    "log"
    
    "github.com/insuretech/go-sdk/pkg/client"
    "github.com/insuretech/go-sdk/pkg/models"
)

func main() {
    // Initialize client
    c := client.NewClient(
        client.WithAPIKey("your-api-key"),
    )
    
    ctx := context.Background()
    
    // Create a policy
    policy, err := c.Policies.Create(ctx, &models.PolicyCreationRequest{
        ProductID:  "prod_123",
        CustomerID: "cust_456",
        Premium:    1200.00,
    })
    if err != nil {
        log.Fatal(err)
    }
    
    fmt.Printf("Created policy: %s\n", policy.PolicyID)
}
```

