## Configuration

### Environment Variables

```bash
export INSURETECH_API_KEY="your-api-key"
export INSURETECH_BASE_URL="https://api.insuretech.com"
```

### Client Options

```go
client := client.NewClient(
    client.WithAPIKey("api-key"),              // API key authentication
    client.WithBaseURL("https://api.insuretech.com"), // Custom base URL
    client.WithTimeout(30 * time.Second),      // Request timeout
    client.WithRetry(3, 1*time.Second),        // Retry configuration
    client.WithOAuth2("oauth-token"),          // OAuth2 authentication
)
```

## Error Handling

```go
policy, err := c.Policies.Get(ctx, "policy_123")
if err != nil {
    if apiErr, ok := err.(*errors.APIError); ok {
        // Handle API errors
        if apiErr.IsNotFound() {
            fmt.Println("Policy not found")
        } else if apiErr.IsUnauthorized() {
            fmt.Println("Authentication failed")
        } else if apiErr.IsRateLimited() {
            fmt.Println("Rate limit exceeded")
        }
    }
    return err
}
```

## Examples

### Creating a Policy

```go
policy, err := c.Policies.Create(ctx, &models.PolicyCreationRequest{
    ProductID:     "prod_health_001",
    CustomerID:    "cust_123",
    Premium:       150.00,
    CoverageAmount: 100000.00,
    StartDate:     time.Now(),
    EndDate:       time.Now().AddDate(1, 0, 0),
})
```

### Processing a Claim

```go
claim, err := c.Claims.Create(ctx, &models.ClaimSubmissionRequest{
    PolicyID:    "policy_789",
    ClaimType:   "medical",
    Amount:      5000.00,
    Description: "Hospital treatment",
})
```

### Generating a Quote

```go
quote, err := c.Quotes.Create(ctx, &models.RequestQuoteRequest{
    ProductID:    "prod_auto_001",
    VehicleYear:  2022,
    VehicleValue: 25000.00,
    DriverAge:    30,
})
```

See the [examples directory](examples/) for more detailed samples.

